   Dribble to Stop Diabetes
   Bankers Life Fieldhouse

   Join us March 20 as we [27]Dribble to Stop Diabetes!

   We'll be at the [28]Indiana Pacers home game to encourage basketball
   fans to live an active, healthy lifestyle and raise awareness about
   diabetes prevention, management and the potentially serious health
   complications that can be associated with the disease.
   Every 20 seconds -- the time it takes for a timeout in a basketball
   game -- someone in the U.S. is diagnosed with diabetes. It's important
   to know your risk and, if you are at risk, talk to your doctor and get
   tested. Visit [29]www.dribbletostopdiabetes.com for more information
   and to take the risk assessment.
   Dribble to Stop Diabetes is brought to you by the National Basketball
   Association (NBA), the Women's National Basketball Association (WNBA)
   and the NBA Development League, in collaboration with the American
   Diabetes Association and Sanofi US.
   Come out to see the Pacers take on the Los Angeles Clippers at Bankers
   Life Fieldhouse on March 20 -- and while you're there, check out our
   educational materials for fans and on-court activities to raise
   awareness about diabetes!

   Date: Tuesday, March 20, 2012
   Time: 7:00 PM - 9:30 PM
   Address:
   125 South Pennsylvania Street
   Indianapolis, IN 46204
   United States

   This event does not require an RSVP. Registered users can request event
   reminders.
